body:
File: compiler/js-native-context-specialization.cc
Symbol: JSNativeContextSpecialization::Reduce (handles various JS ops including JSEqual folding to ObjectIsUndetectable when one side null/undefined if present?)
Excerpt: Search shows JSNativeContextSpecialization contains many reductions; JSEqual specific handling lives in js-typed-lowering.cc; JSNativeContextSpecialization registers protector dependencies in some reductions (e.g., PromiseHook, MegaDOMProtector).
explanation: Record pointing to JSNativeContextSpecialization as a general place for JS op folding (context specialization). Not direct JSEqual folding, but relevant for dependencies like DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector used elsewhere.
